article.headline: Tulane 74, UAB 69
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Marcus Kinzer scored a career-high 19 points to lead Tulane to a 74-69 win over UAB Wednesday night. Vytas Tatarunas added 15 points and 11 rebounds for the Green Wave (11-13, 4-9 Conference USA), while Quincy Davis had 13 points and grabbed 13 rebounds. Dan Fitzgerald rounded out the double-figure scorers with 10 points. Mo Finley led UAB (16-8, 9-4) with 22 points and Demario Eddins added 17. The Blazers took their first lead since the first half on a pair of free throws from Carldell Johnson with 2:29 to go. But a driving scoop by Kinzer put the Wave back on top with 1:43 to go. On the next play, Kinzer stripped Demario Eddins in the paint and found Quincy Davis breaking to the hoop. Davis was fouled but converted both free throws to make it 68-65 at the 1:08 mark. UAB tried to tie the game, but Finley's jumper was off the mark. Tatarunas grabbed the rebound and passed it to Kinzer, who was immediately fouled. Kinzer, who was 7-of-8 from the line, buried both shots and it was 70-68 with 47.9 seconds remaining. The Wave would go on to make four more free throws to seal the victory.
